mcqs.question:
What is the output of the following code?
#define SQR(x) x*x
int main() { printf("%d", SQR(5+1)); }

What will be the output?
enum {A=5, B, C};
printf("%d %d", B, C);

What is the value stored in variable x?
#define SQR(x) (x)*(x)
int x = SQR(3+2);

What is the output?
char c = 'A';
printf("%c", c+1);
